Are there tall buildings near your home?
Not really. I live in a suburban area, so there aren't many high-rise buildings around. Most homes are just one or two storeys, which makes the area feel quite spacious and peaceful.

Do you take photos of buildings?
It really depends. I tend to take photos of historical or cultural buildings because I'm quite interested in history. They often have unique designs and stories behind them, which I find fastinating. But for modern office buildings, not really - they all look quite similar to me.

Is there a building that you would like to visit?
I'd love to visit the Eiffel Tower. It's such an iconic structure, and I've only ever seen it in pictures. I think seeing it up close, especially at night when it's lit up, would be absolutely amazing.
